# 🚀 Project: Linux Server Setup & Automation (Beginner → Job-ready)

## 🎯 What this project shows

* Linux commands (real usage, not theory)
* User & permission management
* Package installation
* Bash scripting
* Basic DevOps mindset

---

# 🧩 Step-by-Step Project Plan

## 🔹 Step 1: Set up Linux environment

Install:

* Ubuntu (VM using VirtualBox) OR
* Windows Subsystem for Linux

Commands to verify:

```bash
uname -a
ls
pwd
```

---

## 🔹 Step 2: Create a project folder

```bash
mkdir linux-project
cd linux-project
```

---

## 🔹 Step 3: User & Permission Management

Create a new user:

```bash
sudo adduser devuser
```

Give sudo access:

```bash
sudo usermod -aG sudo devuser
```

Switch user:

```bash
su - devuser
```

👉 Practice:

```bash
whoami
groups
```

---

## 🔹 Step 4: Install & Manage Services

Install Apache:

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install apache2 -y
```

Check service:

```bash
systemctl status apache2
```

Enable at boot:

```bash
sudo systemctl enable apache2
```

Test:

* Open browser → `http://localhost`

---

## 🔹 Step 5: Create a Simple Website

```bash
cd /var/www/html
sudo nano index.html
```

Add:

```html
<h1>Hello from Linux Server 🚀</h1>
```

---

## 🔹 Step 6: File Permissions Practice

```bash
ls -l
sudo chmod 755 index.html
sudo chown devuser:devuser index.html
```

---

## 🔹 Step 7: Write a Bash Automation Script

Create script:

```bash
nano setup.sh
```

Add:

```bash
#!/bin/bash

echo "Updating system..."
sudo apt update

echo "Installing Apache..."
sudo apt install apache2 -y

echo "Starting Apache..."
sudo systemctl start apache2

echo "Done!"
```

Make executable:

```bash
chmod +x setup.sh
./setup.sh
```

---

## 🔹 Step 8: Log Monitoring

```bash
cd /var/log
ls
tail -f syslog
```

Apache logs:

```bash
cd /var/log/apache2
```

---

## 🔹 Step 9: Disk & Process Monitoring

```bash
df -h
top
ps aux
```

Kill process:

```bash
kill -9 <PID>
```

---

## 🔹 Step 10: Backup Script (Important for Resume ⭐)

```bash
nano backup.sh
```

```bash
#!/bin/bash

tar -czvf backup.tar.gz /var/www/html
echo "Backup completed"
```

